-- Clear Channel agrees to nearly $19 billion sale
-- 
-- Thu Nov 16, 2006 8:42am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2006/11/16/us-media-clearchannel-statement-idUSWEN996220061116

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Clear Channel Communications, Inc. ( CCU.N ) said on Thursday that it agreed to sell itself for $37.60 per share, or nearly $19 billion, to Thomas H. Lee Partners L.P. and Bain Capital Partners LLC. 

 The deal is worth $26.7 billion including $8 billion in debt, the company said.